Rating: 4
Have made this twice and each time I varied the recipe and had great results. The first variance was using part orange extract and part almond extract instead of all almond extract. The second time I made it for a friend who has egg and wheat allergies. I omitted the tart shell completely. The filling made its own shell which was a bit crumbly but excellent anyways. When the ring was taken off the tart pan you couldn't tell that it didn't have a tart shell. I also subsituted black walnut and orange extracts instead of the almond extract. The other changes were to replace the wheat flour with 1/4 cup rice flour, replace the eggs with 1/4 cup of pureed canned pears with 1/4 tsp each of baking soda and baking powder to leaven. This version turned out just as wonderful as the first tart. A great dessert for someone with these kinds of food allergies.

