This tart was outstanding -- gorgeous, sophisticated, delicious and not overly sweet! The crust is fabulous -- buttery and flaky. While it's a bit difficult to work with, it's definitely worth the trouble. I baked the tart Thanksgiving morning and while it was very good that day, we found it was even better the next day! The flavors had time to mellow and blend together and to my amazement, the crust stayed very crisp and flaky. Make sure your pears are perfectly ripe. Mine weren't, so I poached the halves in a very light sugar syrup flavored with a little vanilla and lemon until they were easily pierced with a skewer. Came out great, and don't throw away the syrup; strain, refrigerate and use it to sweeten hot or iced tea. Yum. Brushed the baked pears with a little melted apple jelly (had no apricot preserves). Tasted great; looked beautiful.

