To reduce or eliminate the grainy nature of the hazelnuts, simply roast them slower and longer to eliminate some of their moisture. Be careful not to burn them, but they taste good with a little color, too.

Rating: 0
To a cook from Minneapolis, I've seen it done both ways, but I think it's best to pre-bake the crust, at least part of the way. When I've made this without blind-baking the crust, the crust turns out soggy. I would prepare the crust as the recipe says, but bake it for only the initial 20 minutes, then let it cool, fill it, and return it to the oven.

